    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `exists()` function [f_exists](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ef44e597294e4d0d9128ef69b6aa7481a54e17cb/src/nvim/eval/funcs.c#L1654) cannot currently report on whether a Lua function exists.\r\n\r\nUnder the assumption that both `coc#status` and `v:lua.myLuaFunc` exist:\r\n\r\n> **Note**\r\n> `exists('*coc#status')` == 1\r\n\r\n> **Warning**\r\n> `exists('*v:lua.myLuaFunc')` --> E15: Invalid expression: v:lua\r\n\r\nRef: https://github.com/itchyny/lightline.vim/issues/657#issuecomment-1666663760\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n> **Note**\r\n> `exists('*v:lua.myLuaFunc')` == 1\r\n>  :white_check_mark: ",
