        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Besides the context of the original plugin, as a Vim script plugin author, the expectation here is simple; having a function name `f`, `exists('*' . f)` yields 1 if it exists. This applies to user-defined dict functions too (of course).\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nfunction! F()\r\n  echo 'F'\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\ncall F()\r\necho exists('*F')\r\n\r\nlet G = {}\r\nfunction! G.F()\r\n  echo 'G.F'\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\ncall G.F()\r\necho exists('*G.F')\r\n```",
